dcterms:description: The CMS data sets contain mainly three types of information: hospitalization requests (Inpatient Data), outpatient care requests (Outpatient Data), and beneficiary information (Beneficiary Details Data). The dataset includes information such as the identifier of the beneficiary (BeneID), the identifier of the claims (ClaimID), the unique identifier of the healthcare provider (NPI), and the refunded amount (AmtReimbursed).
dcterms:title: CMS Data (2017–2019)

dcterms:description: The LEIE table contains the list of healthcare providers excluded from the healthcare system for illegitimate or fraudulent activities. This dataset is used to identify fraudulent providers in the context of Medicare fraud detection.
dcterms:title: Office of Inspector General’s List of Excluded Individuals and Entities (LEIE)
